Definition.WordDefinition: Ha-ha \Ha-ha"\ (h[aum]*h[aum]"), n. [See {Haw-haw}.] A sunk fence; a fence, wall, or ditch, not visible till one is close upon it. [Written also {haw-haw}.] [1913 Webster]

ha-ha n 1: a loud laugh that sounds like a horse neighing [syn: {hee-haw}, {horselaugh}, {haw-haw}] 2: a ditch with one side being a retaining wall; used to divide lands without defacing the landscape [syn: {sunk fence}, {haw-haw}]
